Amy and I work each case
independently of one another.

01:52.466 --> 01:54.536
I interview living witnesses

01:54.538 --> 01:57.341
and uncover secrets
about the property's past

01:57.343 --> 01:59.811
while Amy communicates
with the dead.

02:03.887 --> 02:05.424
I'm in Rome, New York.

02:05.426 --> 02:07.463
It's about an hour
east of Syracuse.

02:07.465 --> 02:09.699
Amy and I got called in
by a young married couple,

02:09.701 --> 02:10.868
Sue and Joe.

02:10.870 --> 02:13.272
They didn't sound very good
on the phone.

02:13.274 --> 02:15.543
The activity's so bad
and so physical,

02:15.545 --> 02:17.814
Sue had moved out
with the three kids.

02:17.816 --> 02:18.950
But now she's back.

02:18.952 --> 02:21.323
She says if we can't help her
find a way

02:21.325 --> 02:24.192
to make the activity stop,
it may end her marriage.

02:24.194 --> 02:26.829
I'm really hoping
Amy and I can help them out.

02:32.670 --> 02:34.905
Before Amy arrives,

02:34.907 --> 02:38.079
I clear the area
of any leading information.

02:38.081 --> 02:40.914
Family photos
and other personal items

02:40.916 --> 02:43.015
need to be covered or removed.

02:43.017 --> 02:47.218
When I'm done, the location will
be ready for tonight's walk.

02:58.434 --> 03:00.536
So in my opening,

03:00.538 --> 03:07.044
I saw all of these thick trees,

03:07.046 --> 03:10.213
and there were all these
native American warriors

03:10.215 --> 03:13.148
standing there
with their bow and arrow drawn.

03:17.457 --> 03:20.859
They're waiting
for something to happen.

03:20.861 --> 03:24.329
They were put there
by this leader guy.

03:24.331 --> 03:28.967
He says it is some kind of,
like, spirit warfare.

03:33.941 --> 03:39.880
He says that there were problems
before the white man,

03:39.882 --> 03:44.654
that they had a lot of battles,
many battles,

03:44.656 --> 03:47.722
with these spirits.

03:55.859 --> 03:59.731
Sue, you sounded
clearly upset on the phone.

03:59.733 --> 04:03.237
Give me an idea
of what you're going through.

04:05.272 --> 04:08.941
We hear banging, knocking,
footsteps.

04:08.943 --> 04:11.111
I've seen apparitions.

04:11.113 --> 04:12.681
I've been physically touched.

04:12.683 --> 04:15.521
I've tried to rationalize
with myself

04:15.523 --> 04:17.490
a million times over again.

04:17.492 --> 04:19.491
I have tried to make up
every excuse in the book

04:19.493 --> 04:21.558
other than it being paranormal.

04:21.560 --> 04:23.861
Now, do you
believe in this stuff?

04:23.863 --> 04:25.631
What really made me
believe in it

04:25.633 --> 04:27.369
was when
my 8-year-old daughter,

04:27.371 --> 04:30.811
you know, she heard people
talking, whispering.

04:30.813 --> 04:32.313
- Is this your kids here?
- Yes.

04:33.882 --> 04:35.048
Now, who's who?

04:35.050 --> 04:36.249
This is Madison.

04:36.251 --> 04:37.184
Okay.

04:37.186 --> 04:39.321
That's Brooke Lynn and Joey.

04:39.323 --> 04:41.858
You had actually left with
the kids at one point, right?

04:41.860 --> 04:42.693
Yes.

04:42.695 --> 04:46.167
I moved out for 11 months.

04:47.838 --> 04:50.572
I just couldn't take it
anymore.

04:50.574 --> 04:53.177
They do not like to be alone.

04:53.179 --> 04:56.783
- So did you take them out
to protect them? - Yes.

04:56.785 --> 04:59.053
I don't want my kids
to grow up experiencing

04:59.055 --> 05:01.889
anything that I have.

05:03.292 --> 05:06.863
What made you come back home?

05:06.865 --> 05:09.469
I wanted my family back.

05:09.471 --> 05:13.412
I don't want them
to be from a broken home.

05:13.414 --> 05:14.780
But you came back to hell.

05:14.782 --> 05:15.781
Yeah.

05:15.783 --> 05:17.451
The same as it was
before I left.

05:17.453 --> 05:21.224
Have you guys ever thought
about just moving?

05:21.226 --> 05:23.528
That would be last resort
only because

05:23.530 --> 05:25.798
my husband inherited it
from his grandparents,

05:25.800 --> 05:28.866
so he's got
an emotional attachment.

05:31.972 --> 05:33.773
This native American guy

05:33.775 --> 05:37.512
says that there is some kind
of a family of beasts,

05:37.514 --> 05:41.576
and they think
that they're ghosts.

05:41.578 --> 05:45.815
These things are occasionally
trying to enter the house.

05:49.154 --> 05:52.089
They're very dark,

05:52.091 --> 05:55.658
and they look kind of like
human beings,

05:55.660 --> 05:58.296
but they're definitely not.

05:58.298 --> 05:59.831
Were they living?

05:59.833 --> 06:01.735
I don't know yet.

06:01.737 --> 06:04.837
They just look creepy.

06:10.174 --> 06:13.277
Okay, so why'd you
bring me in the kitchen?

06:13.279 --> 06:15.613
Well, we hear knocking
at the door.

06:15.615 --> 06:17.146
Okay.

06:17.148 --> 06:19.512
Get up, answer it,
nobody there.

06:19.514 --> 06:20.414
Okay.

06:20.416 --> 06:22.584
So, is anything else going on?

06:22.586 --> 06:25.022
Banging.

06:25.024 --> 06:27.893
It's a... bang! Bang!
Bang! Bang! Bang!

06:27.895 --> 06:29.192
Where does it sound like
it's coming from?

06:29.194 --> 06:31.926
The far right corner
of the living room.

06:31.928 --> 06:33.659
If something's wrong
with the pressure in the pipes,

06:33.661 --> 06:34.659
that would bang.

06:34.661 --> 06:36.594
All of our pipes
are in the basement.

06:36.596 --> 06:38.331
And does it happen
at any given time?

06:38.333 --> 06:39.534
Mainly at night.

06:39.536 --> 06:41.236
Well, that's got to scare
the hell out of you.

06:41.238 --> 06:42.603
Startles you.

06:42.605 --> 06:45.235
I mean, you'll jump out of
your skin when you hear it.

06:48.203 --> 06:52.540
These things are pretty tall.

06:52.542 --> 06:54.643
How tall?

06:54.645 --> 06:56.944
Well, see where
that dent thing is?

06:59.745 --> 07:01.778
About that tall.

07:01.780 --> 07:05.818
Their head kind of jets forward
on a long neck,

07:05.820 --> 07:07.154
and they're hunched,

07:07.156 --> 07:09.988
and you can really see
their shoulder blades.

07:09.990 --> 07:13.488
And also, they have, like,
a spine thing that sticks out.

07:13.490 --> 07:17.692
And then really long arms
with the long fingers.

07:17.694 --> 07:24.564
It's like a weird dragging sound
against the house.

07:28.833 --> 07:31.937
Do you have any idea how
the living might perceive them?

07:31.939 --> 07:35.038
Making noises
on the outside of the house,

07:35.040 --> 07:38.537
looking in through windows,
growling.

07:38.539 --> 07:40.170
Do you know what they want?

07:40.172 --> 07:43.641
They definitely have their
sights set on the children here.

07:46.679 --> 07:49.813
Maybe these are what
the native American warriors

07:49.815 --> 07:51.915
- are fending off?
- Hm.

07:51.917 --> 07:56.054
Maybe they are trying
to protect kids?

08:01.555 --> 08:06.758
I hear footsteps
walking in here at night.

08:06.760 --> 08:08.561
So it sounds like
it's in the room with you?

08:08.563 --> 08:09.462
Mm-hmm.

08:09.464 --> 08:11.131
Okay.
You have the TV in here now.

08:11.133 --> 08:12.599
- Do you keep the TV on?
- No.

08:12.601 --> 08:14.265
And there's no sounds
coming from upstairs,

08:14.267 --> 08:15.999
- like the kids walking around, or...
- No.

08:16.001 --> 08:18.269
Is anything else going on?

08:18.271 --> 08:21.475
Aside from being touched
a few times, no.

08:21.477 --> 08:23.678
What do you mean "touched"?

08:23.680 --> 08:26.313
Well, there was an incident
in the shower one time

08:26.315 --> 08:27.913
where I felt like
somebody had rubbed

08:27.915 --> 08:29.312
the outer part of my right arm.

08:29.314 --> 08:31.615
And there was another time...

08:31.617 --> 08:33.852
in the living room,
on the couch.

08:33.854 --> 08:35.155
Okay, what happened?

08:35.158 --> 08:40.827
I felt this... grope.

08:40.828 --> 08:43.361
So I'm assuming
it was forceful.

08:43.363 --> 08:45.296
Okay.

08:45.298 --> 08:48.202
Being touched,
it's a violation.

08:48.204 --> 08:51.205
Not only for me,
but for my husband.

08:51.207 --> 08:54.372
I will do whatever I have to do
to make sure that my kids

08:54.374 --> 08:57.206
do not experience
what I have experienced.

08:59.912 --> 09:04.854
They definitely messed
with the boy who lives here.

09:07.589 --> 09:09.623
In this one,
I just hear crying.

09:09.625 --> 09:14.763
Crying and things like touching.
Ooh.

09:14.765 --> 09:17.600
This is not good.

09:17.602 --> 09:18.433
Oh

09:18.435 --> 09:19.768
Like, trying to hide,

09:19.770 --> 09:22.402
and those weird [Bleep]
finger [Bleep] or whatever.

09:25.004 --> 09:28.512
He was crying
'cause he was scared.

09:28.514 --> 09:32.081
So, you mentioned you
were worried about the kids.

09:32.083 --> 09:34.213
What's going on with them?

09:34.215 --> 09:36.782
Well, Joey...
he's more of just...

09:36.784 --> 09:38.786
Scared to go upstairs alone.

09:38.788 --> 09:40.890
Brooke Lynn
also is the same way,

09:40.892 --> 09:42.927
but she seems to be
a little bit more sensitive.

09:42.929 --> 09:44.562
She's hearing voices.

09:44.564 --> 09:48.828
I wonder if she's being affected
more than I know.

09:48.830 --> 09:53.002
I don't want them to grow up
and be scared.

09:53.004 --> 09:56.675
You know, my worst fear
is that they might get worse.

09:56.677 --> 09:58.674
This is home to them,

09:58.676 --> 10:01.107
and they shouldn't be afraid.

10:03.111 --> 10:05.716
Well, for some
[Bleep] up reason,

10:05.718 --> 10:07.386
dead people come here.

10:07.388 --> 10:11.288
I see this dead woman.

10:11.290 --> 10:13.622
She's kneeling on the floor
right here.

10:13.624 --> 10:16.026
She's only one of many...
many of them.

10:18.832 --> 10:21.969
I think the creatures here
have never been human,

10:21.971 --> 10:24.602
but now I'm seeing dead people
lined up,

10:24.604 --> 10:26.871
and they're seeking help
from a living person.

10:26.873 --> 10:30.680
This person here might have...

10:30.682 --> 10:34.084
ohh... an idea
that they are a medium.

10:34.086 --> 10:38.318
Dead people
coming to get moved on.

10:38.320 --> 10:40.222
This is not good for them.

10:40.224 --> 10:42.058
No, this kid's got to go.

11:04.843 --> 11:05.910
Joe, your wife, Sue,

11:05.912 --> 11:08.344
said that you actually grew up
in this house as a kid.

11:08.346 --> 11:11.783
My grandparents used to live
in this house when I was a kid.

11:11.785 --> 11:14.087
- I grew up across the street.
- Okay.

11:14.089 --> 11:15.891
So, I was always over here.

11:15.893 --> 11:18.191
Did you have experiences
as a kid here?

11:18.193 --> 11:20.459
You know,
a couple different times,

11:20.461 --> 11:23.195
but I kind of blew it off as,
you know, it's no big deal.

11:23.197 --> 11:24.933
So your grandparents, I assume,

11:24.935 --> 11:27.972
- the way you're talking now,
they both passed away? - Yeah.

11:27.974 --> 11:29.807
My grandmother passed in 1997.

11:29.809 --> 11:32.308
She had developed emphysema,

11:32.310 --> 11:35.243
and then the emphysema
led to bone cancer.

11:35.245 --> 11:38.949
She passed away in the house,
under hospice care.

11:38.951 --> 11:39.784
Okay.

11:39.786 --> 11:41.885
What kind of woman was she?

11:41.887 --> 11:44.085
She treated me like, you know,
her little prince,

11:44.087 --> 11:45.152
to be honest with you,

11:45.154 --> 11:46.955
and that's how she always
made me feel.

11:46.957 --> 11:49.960
She made me feel loved.

11:49.962 --> 11:54.232
Very kindhearted lady.
Loved to cook.

11:54.234 --> 11:55.698
I mean, I miss her cooking.

11:55.700 --> 11:57.399
You know,
she was my role model.

11:57.401 --> 12:00.103
When Grandma passed on,
it was very hard for me.

12:03.359 --> 12:05.830
I'm getting this older woman.

12:05.832 --> 12:08.368
She was always cooking
and cleaning in here.

12:08.370 --> 12:09.368
She was little.

12:09.370 --> 12:13.203
Tiny, little lady.
Very frail.

12:13.205 --> 12:18.443
And she's putzing around,
putzing around.

12:18.445 --> 12:21.981
She's, I don't know, related
to somebody here or something?

12:21.983 --> 12:24.216
Living?

12:24.218 --> 12:25.918
Yes.

12:27.387 --> 12:31.425
Now, Joe, when did
your grandfather die?

12:31.427 --> 12:35.198
He died September 10, 2001,
the day before 9/11.

12:35.200 --> 12:36.098
Wow.

12:36.100 --> 12:38.367
I'm not sure how he passed on.

12:38.369 --> 12:41.436
There was never
an autopsy done.

12:41.438 --> 12:44.475
I think that he had
a massive heart attack.

12:44.477 --> 12:47.613
He was a hard-core smoker,
three packs a day.

12:47.615 --> 12:50.715
He actually passed away
right here in the kitchen,

12:50.717 --> 12:52.918
and he was, you know,
dead on the floor.

12:52.920 --> 12:54.419
Okay.

12:54.421 --> 12:56.255
Do you know how old
grandpa was when he died?

12:56.257 --> 12:57.425
75.

12:57.427 --> 12:59.695
Okay, so what kind of a guy
was your grandfather?

12:59.947 --> 13:02.715
He was a Sicilian-American
immigrant.

13:02.717 --> 13:05.519
He was very tough, hard-nosed,
old-school Italian.

13:05.521 --> 13:07.323
Somebody that I looked up to.

13:07.325 --> 13:09.294
I actually have a picture here

13:09.296 --> 13:12.132
of him and I
from when I was a little guy.

13:12.134 --> 13:14.800
Joe, you obviously
knew your grandparents

13:14.802 --> 13:16.701
- better than anybody.
- Right.

13:16.703 --> 13:17.969
Would they want you

13:17.971 --> 13:20.104
to stay here and fight
whatever the hell is going on?

13:20.106 --> 13:21.875
They wouldn't want me
to give up.

13:21.877 --> 13:23.111
Right.

13:23.113 --> 13:25.447
They would want me to fight
for what is mine.

13:25.449 --> 13:29.648
And they instilled in me,
you know, you never give up.

13:35.359 --> 13:38.626
I see, like,
some kids running by.

13:38.628 --> 13:43.063
A little girl
and, I think, a little boy.

13:43.065 --> 13:46.832
They're probably
between, like, 5 and 8?

13:46.834 --> 13:50.938
Somebody here is watching them.

13:50.940 --> 13:54.675
I think that this is a male.

13:54.677 --> 13:58.513
He's pretty dang old.
He's probably like 70 maybe.

13:58.515 --> 14:01.082
Yeah, I think he's Italian.

14:01.084 --> 14:02.519
A heavy, heavy smoker.

14:02.521 --> 14:04.555
He's not a bad guy.

14:04.557 --> 14:06.858
Do you know when he's from?

14:06.860 --> 14:11.397
Maybe he died
in, like, the '90s?

14:11.399 --> 14:15.469
1990s? Early 2000?

14:15.471 --> 14:17.270
Do you know how he died?

14:17.272 --> 14:19.406
I think he had a heart attack.

14:19.408 --> 14:21.041
Maybe it was emphysema,

14:21.043 --> 14:25.213
'cause I can't [Bleep] breathe
for [Bleep] from him.

14:31.382 --> 14:34.952
So, Joe, what made you
bring me out here?

14:34.954 --> 14:36.321
I was inside, and I noticed,

14:36.323 --> 14:39.527
off to the right-hand side,
over here,

14:39.529 --> 14:40.796
there was two mirrors,

14:40.798 --> 14:42.967
and I noticed
that both of 'em cracked

14:42.969 --> 14:44.369
and was just stunned.

14:44.371 --> 14:46.669
Kind of really frightened me,
to be honest with you.

14:46.671 --> 14:48.935
So, did anything hit it that
would have caused it to crack?

14:48.937 --> 14:51.905
There was nothing that
could have been thrown at it,

14:51.907 --> 14:53.140
nothing that hit it.

14:53.142 --> 14:55.944
It wasn't broke
when I looked at it

14:55.946 --> 14:57.746
three minutes
prior to this happening.

14:57.748 --> 14:59.015
Okay.

14:59.017 --> 15:00.447
Let me ask you a question, Joe.

15:00.449 --> 15:02.282
What are you trying to get
out of our investigation?

15:02.284 --> 15:03.817
What's the best thing
we could do for you?

15:03.819 --> 15:06.153
I don't want the kids
to be affected.

15:06.155 --> 15:08.924
I don't want to have to keep
things from them.

15:08.926 --> 15:11.828
You know, as a dad
and as a father,

15:11.830 --> 15:14.527
I just want to be there
to protect them.

15:14.529 --> 15:16.262
I just want things to stop.

15:16.264 --> 15:18.298
It's been tough
on your marriage.

15:18.300 --> 15:21.870
Yeah, it's been tough.
It's weighed pretty hard.

15:21.872 --> 15:24.307
You know, it's tough
to talk about those things

15:24.309 --> 15:27.176
because she means
everything to me,

15:27.178 --> 15:30.379
and without her,
I would have no family.

15:30.381 --> 15:32.548
Since she has come back,
you know,

15:32.550 --> 15:34.549
she's been touched and whatnot,

15:34.551 --> 15:37.051
and I just want a safe spot
for my family.

15:37.053 --> 15:38.919
That's all that I want, really.

15:54.095 --> 15:55.732
I combed through
my client's property records,

15:55.734 --> 15:57.201
and as it turns out,

15:57.203 --> 16:00.071
a family lived on the land
for 50 years.

16:00.073 --> 16:02.842
Most of the time,
this doesn't amount to much,

16:02.844 --> 16:04.511
but I spoke
to a local genealogist

16:04.513 --> 16:06.613
who told me the family
that lived on the land

16:06.615 --> 16:09.784
suffered enough tragedy
to last ten lifetimes.

16:18.831 --> 16:20.299
Kobler family...

16:20.301 --> 16:23.636
they lived on my client's
property for almost 50 years.

16:23.638 --> 16:25.739
From about 1874 to 1919.

16:25.741 --> 16:27.508
Now, when we spoke
on the phone,

16:27.510 --> 16:29.478
you said that there
were some terrible times

16:29.480 --> 16:31.747
- on the property when they were there.
- There was.

16:31.749 --> 16:34.685
It all seems to center around
